		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1221975">
                  
                  terrible news indeed.<br />
<br />
what a way to trash such a great system (spell ID) on raids.<br />
<br />
great so we get to see what a raid mob is casting via spell ID but can do nothing about it?<br />
<br />
<font color="Red"><b>Fixing spell counters on raids.</b></font><br />
<br />
<b>#1 all caster classes have spell counters (druid/necro/bm/sorc/psi)<br />
all of them can dismiss the spell being casted.<br />
<br />
#2 Place a spell ID counter # next to the spell being casted.  This would require multiple classes to counter the incomming spell.  Also require different types of spell ID counters.  Also redundant counters are not counted.  IE three druids cant spell counter by themselves, only 1 counter from 1 druid would count.<br />
<br />
#3 Make the cast times on the mob abilities really short like less than 2.0 seconds.<br />
<br />
Example #1<br />
Mob starts to cast nuke of devesation<br />
spell ID fires for any casters who catch it.<br />
1.5s cast time, and requires 4 spell counters to dismiss the nuke.</b><br />
<br />
--Since sorc have disperse/reflect and are more *anti caster/magic* only our 2 counters will count seperatly.  and the other 2 would need to be filled by two other caster classes, IE druid/nec/psi/bm<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<font color="Cyan"><b>Fixing wards for raid content.</b></font><br />
<br />
<font color="Cyan">#1 separate out raid mob abilities into two category's. </font><br />
-Mele ability<br />
-Spell ability<br />
<br />
<font color="Red"><b>Nulling ward </b></font>- dismisses 1 mele ability, the same target can not be affected by nulling ward for another XX seconds (30s 60s ...ect)<br />
<br />
<font color="red"><b>Reflect ward </b></font>- reflects 1 spell ability, the same target can not be affected by reflect ward for another XX seconds (1min -2min - 5min ect)<br />
<br />
<font color="cyan">#2 Create a &quot;lesser&quot; version of each spell ability (IE 90% reduction 95% reduction across the board...ect)</font><br />
<br />
Then when a mob uses a spell ability and it gets reflected, it will hit for the &quot;lesser&quot; version back on the mob.<br />
<br />
<font color="cyan">#3 Allow chromantic barrier to reflect 1 spell ability every 60 seconds (its normal refresh)</font><br />
<br />
--this would give sorcer'ers the ability to ward themselves against an additional spell ability, in keeping with our anti magic theme.<br />
<br />
<font color="Cyan">#4 Fix Chromantic Halo to allow a reduction in the % of incomming spell damage</font><br />
<br />
--This can be anything you guys tune, 5%-10%, 15% ect.  This would be a permenant 60min buff that reduces incomming spell damage from ALL types by a set %.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
