I dont play a cleric.  I also have never seen a 1 hour long group ward come from one of them.<br />
<br />
I'm talking about making our wards useful for raids.  <br />
<br />
Here's how I see them working out with the changes I've given.<br />
<br />
#1 we can give 1 AE avoid to our group within 10m vs mele abilities every XX seconds (devs can specify length)<br />
#2 we can give 1 AE avoid to our group within 10m vs spell abilities every XX seconds (devs can specify)<br />
<br />
This is a great comprimise to our wards for raid and group/solo, and the best part is mechanics to change it are already in place (lockout on recasting abilities in xx amount of time)<br />
<br />
<br />
To emilia, <br />
They can design around it like you suggested by making pulse ae's or by putting in a crap attack justbefore a big one, but then again we would be the only class capable of doing so, and then only within the limits they set.<br />
<br />
Hell it could be once per 5 min (once per fight)  we all know that AE's are generally timed / scripted and go off many times per fight  reducing one AE or attack or power drain, or raid debuff, is not that important in the grand scheme of things.
                  
